<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>No. 190 
                    The Acting Secretary of State to
                        the Ambassador in the United Kingdom (
                        Winant
                    )</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv01</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d190</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">190</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-07-06T17:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-07-06T17:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-06T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-06T17:00:00-05:00" n="190" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d190">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 <gloss target="#t_EW1">EW</gloss>/6–2345: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 190 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WJG2" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]<note n="1" xml:id="d190fn1">For the full text
                            of this message, see <ref target="#d303">document No. 303</ref>.</note>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-06T18:00:00-04:00">July 6, 1945—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5517. …</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                <p>You may accordingly tell <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> that … at
                    forthcoming highest-level discussions we intend to press strongly proposals for
                    implementation of Yalta Declaration<note n="2" xml:id="d190fn2">On Liberated
                        Europe. See <ref target="frus1945Berlinv02#d1417">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, document No. 1417, section <hi rend="smallcaps">v</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> and reorganization of <gloss target="#t_ACC1">ACC</gloss>’s
                    in all three ex-satellites. We shall oppose proposals to establish diplomatic
                    relations or conclude peace with present Govts there. …</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
